cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and dependency parsing. It may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves probabilistic models and learning algorithms. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as neural networks are commonly used in dependency parsing, and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it involves algorithmic frameworks for learning statistical models.
